Source: ©LIA LIAThe decsions have been made in the light of the invasion of Ukraine by Russia. The LIA is the latest in a long line of advertising award shows that have taken various steps against Russia or/and in support of the Ukraine.  Barbara Levy, President of LIA, says: “The decision to ban Russian submissions was not made lightly.  As a company, we do not support unjust aggression of any form and are fully behind all efforts for peace. "Therefore, we stand in solidarity with Ukraine and its creative community, in the face of tremendous adversity, the depths of which most of us can only imagine.”Cannes Lions & One Club show support for UkraineBy Danette Breitenbach 7 Mar 2022LIA was created for creatives and remains passionate about celebrating creative work from all over the world and advancing the creative community with continued programs to mentor and coach young creatives. "It is our fervent hope that this war ends quickly and all of our colleagues, their families and friends remain safe and well during these tumultuous times," says Levy.